 <ab type="translation"
  xml:id="p0397_translation"
  corresp="#p0397_transcription">
   <!-- contineus from the previous page -->
   in the bitterness of my soul.
   O Lord, if such be man's life, 
   and the life of my spirit be cast amid such things, 
   Thou wilt chastise me and make me to live: 
   behold, even in peace was my bitterness most bitter. <!-- OBDS page 451 -->
   But Thou hast delivered my soul that it should not perish: 
   Thou hast cast all my sins behind Thy back.
   For hell shall not confess unto Thee, 
   neither shall death praise Thee: 
   nor shall they that go down into the pit look for Thy truth.
   The man that liveth, yea, 
   the man that liveth, he shall praise Thee, 
   even as I do this day: 
   the father shall make known Thy truth unto his children. <!-- OBDS page 452 -->
